    <button class="accordion">What is Permissible Exposure Limits of Hazardous Substances?</button>
    <div class="panel">
        <p>It is the maximum legal limit for the workers working in an industry to get exposed to a particular hazardous substance without any danger to health and safety. </p>
    </div>

    <button class="accordion">How is TWA mgm3 measured?</button>
    <div class="panel">
        <p>It means the maximum average airborne concentration of a substance when calculated over an <b> eight-hour working day, for a five-day working week. </b></p>
    </div>

    <button class="accordion">How does it improve my condition?</button>
    <div class="panel">
        <p>Exposure to hazardous substances than permissible exposure limit causes inhale of contaminated air-borne particles and they rapidly get settled in lungs. Thereby causing lung damage in future times.</p>
    </div>

